    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "When working with `sshfs` or other remote filesystems, sometimes writes take many seconds to complete. It would be nice if the write could be performed asynchronously so the UI remained responsive while that was happening - perhaps because the user wishes to continue work editing another buffer or whatever. On the UI they'd know the write had completed because the `modified` state will disappear.\r\n\r\nTaking inspiration from `:&grep` maybe this could be spelled `:&write` or `:&w`.\r\n\r\nOptionally, a setting to make async writes default on `:w` would be handy too, maybe spelled `:set asyncwrite`",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
